ignition-tools
------------------------------------------
Ignition entry point for using all the suite of ignition tools.

Ignition tools provide the ign command line tool that accepts multiple
subcommands. Each subcommand is implemented in a plugin that belongs to a
specific Ignition project. For example, all the commands that start with ign
topic ... will be implemented by the Ignition Transport library.

Runtime requirements:
  ruby-2.2.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.3.2-1
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.3-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://ignitionrobotics.org/libraries/tools

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ignition-tools-0.0.1+hg20150828-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ignition-tools-0.0.1+hg20150828-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-0.0.1+hg20150828-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-0.0.1+hg20150828-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ignition-tools)
  /usr/bin/ign
  /usr/lib/cmake/ignition-tools/ignition-tools-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ignition-tools.pc
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ignition-tools.README
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/README.md

